This paper deals with the problem of computing winning sets in graph games, which is a fundamental problem in computer aided verification. The techniques used in the paper involve graph algorithms and complexity theory, which are closely related to the areas of logic (cs.LO), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and programming languages (cs.PL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
